            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663691014137-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crush your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don’t have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Combine your <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>and <strong>tamarind paste </strong>in a small bowl with<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and mix it all together – this is your<strong> tamarind sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Balsamic-Vinegar-1665734666727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
